cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "@klodr/gmail-mcp"
abstract: >-
  MCP (Model Context Protocol) server for Gmail with audited safeguards:
  path jails with realpath + O_NOFOLLOW, CRLF sanitization, OAuth scope
  filtering at startup, Zod-bounded inputs, opt-in JSONL audit log,
  per-bucket write rate limits, LLM-output defense fence, attachment
  filename neutralisation, Sigstore + SLSA + SBOM-signed releases.
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Claude
    family-names: Perrin
    alias: klodr
repository-code: "https://github.com/klodr/gmail-mcp"
url: "https://github.com/klodr/gmail-mcp"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - mcp
  - model-context-protocol
  - gmail
  - claude
  - llm
  - email
  - oauth
